--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
INFORMATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Name   : avahi
Type   : Ansible role

Authors: liv community
License: Simplified BSD License

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Avahi is a system which facilitates service discovery on a local network --
this means that you can plug your laptop or computer into a network and
instantly be able to view other people who you can chat with, find printers to
print to or find files being shared. This kind of technology is already found in
MacOS X (branded 'Rendezvous', 'Bonjour' and sometimes 'ZeroConf') and is very
convenient.

For more information on the usage and available configuration options,
consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: avahi
    vars:
      avahi_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: avahi
    vars:
      avahi_state: 'remove'

INACTIVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
      - role: avahi
    vars:
      avahi_state: 'inactive'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PARAMETERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  avahi_state
    Description: Control the state of the role.
    Implemented: 0.1
    Required   : False
    Value      : Predetermined
    Type       : String
    Default    : 'remove'
    Options    :
      Install : 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
      Remove  : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
      Inactive: 'quiesce' | 'inactive'

